      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "BLOOM's primary differentiator is its focus on early childhood development within humanitarian contexts. Since its inception, it has successfully completed <cite id=\"9\">11 PlayGardens</cite>, providing over <cite id=\"12\">800 children with new access to play spaces</cite>. This specialized focus is paired with high transparency, as evidenced by their <cite id=\"7\">Candid Platinum Seal</cite> and a <cite id=\"13\">perfect 100/100 score in Culture & Community</cite> from Charity Navigator."
      ],
      "summary": "Founded in <cite id=\"1\">2017</cite>, BLOOM Charity is a specialized non-profit organization dedicated to advocating for children in crisis through the creation of therapeutic play spaces and enrichment programs. The organization operates with a high degree of financial efficiency, reporting <cite id=\"2\">$158,297 in total revenue</cite> for the 2023 tax year while maintaining a <cite id=\"3\">98.7% program expense ratio</cite>. Their flagship initiative, 'Morocco's Magical PlayGardens,' focuses on the developmental needs of orphans and vulnerable children by providing <cite id=\"4\">daily access to play and the outdoors</cite>. Beyond infrastructure, BLOOM has demonstrated significant agility in crisis response, notably providing <cite id=\"5\">700,000 meals in Gaza</cite> and serving <cite id=\"6\">15,000 families through Agafay Park</cite> as part of their 2024 mobilization efforts. The organization holds a <cite id=\"7\">Platinum Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite> and an <cite id=\"8\">overall score of 89.89.5/100 from Charity Navigator</cite>, reflecting strong organizational health and a commitment to public accountability. By focusing on the often-overlooked psychological and developmental needs of children in conflict zones, BLOOM fills a critical niche in the humanitarian sector, combining direct aid with long-term therapeutic infrastructure like the <cite id=\"9\">11 PlayGardens built to date</cite>.",
